\b\fs40 \cf2 Best for your broadband signal\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\sa321\partightenfactor0

\b0\fs28 \cf2 \
First of all, find your\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://www.google.com/search?q=master+telephone+socket&oq=master+telephone+socket"}}{\fldrslt \cf3 \ul \ulc3 master telephone socket}}. This is the best socket to connect your router to. It\'92s usually closest to where the telephone line comes into your home or office. You don\'92t have to connect your router to this one. But you\'92ll get the best broadband performance from it, especially if you have a poor quality or long line.\
If you find your broadband works just as well in other sockets, go ahead and use them instead. But if you\'92re having problems, like connection dropping regularly, use the master socket whilst you\'92re sorting it out.\
